[size=5][b]Body and Clothing Morph for SBBF and BCB[/b][/size]

Pick a female body shape per character — Vanilla, SBBF, or BCB — and your armor or clothing refits to match.

[url=https://github.com/Shiney1965/BG3-Body-and-Clothing-Morph]Source on GitHub[/url]

[size=4][b]Overview[/b][/size]
Body and Clothing Morph lets you choose a female body shape per character and applies it to the currently controlled character. The choice is stored per character in your savegame and persists across save/load. Your equipped clothing and armor is automatically refitted to the selected body.

You can change the body shape three ways:
[list]
[*]The MCM (Mod Configuration Menu) UI
[*]Console commands (e.g. [font=Courier New]!cm_setbody vanilla|sbbf|bcb[/font])
[*]Optional hotkeys
[/list]

[size=4][b]Features[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][b]Per-character body shape[/b] — Vanilla / SBBF / BCB, applied to the controlled character and saved per character.
[*][b]Automatic clothing/armor refit[/b] to the chosen body.
[*][b]MCM configuration UI[/b] — a "Body shape" radio picker.
[*][b]Console commands[/b] — [font=Courier New]!cm_setbody[/font], plus diagnostics.
[*][b]Optional hotkeys[/b] via MCM keybindings: a "cycle body" key plus direct-set keys for Vanilla / SBBF / BCB. All unbound by default (so they never clash out of the box) — you bind them yourself in MCM.
[*][b]Permission-flag system[/b] that lets other clothing-mod authors opt their items in to being auto-refitted by this mod (see [i]For mod authors[/i] below).
[*]Incorporates clothing mods where permissions allow — SCO, BCB and others (with limitations).
[*]Compatible with BCB and SBBF (with some limits — mod only works on a Tav, not an Origin character).
[/list]

[size=4][b]Requirements[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/baldursgate3/mods/9162]BG3 Mod Configuration Menu (MCM)[/url], by Volitio/AtilioA — NexusMods mod 9162, version 1.19 or newer (required for the hotkey/keybinding feature).
[*]BG3 Script Extender (BG3SE), by Norbyte.
[/list]

[b]For the SBBF body option[/b] — soft requirement (compatible if you want SBBF on NPCs or special SBBF-only clothing):
[list]
[*][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/baldursgate3/mods/4864]SBBF — Stylized Beautiful Body for Female[/url], by FredKarrera — NexusMods mod 4864 (and its [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/baldursgate3/mods/5040]Vanilla Outfits Patch[/url], mod 5040).
[/list]

[b]For the BCB body and BCB clothing[/b] — soft requirement (compatible if you want BCB on NPCs or special BCB-only clothing):
[list]
[*][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/baldursgate3/mods/2351]BCB by Sindae[/url] — NexusMods mod 2351.
[/list]

[b]For the BCB clothing add-on ([font=Courier New]ClothMorphBCB[/font])[/b] — required [b]only if you install that optional add-on[/b]:
[list]
[*][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/baldursgate3/mods/2351]BCB by Sindae[/url] — NexusMods mod 2351. Like the SCO add-on, [font=Courier New]ClothMorphBCB[/font] ships [b]only[/b] the vanilla- and SBBF-fitted refit meshes; the BCB garments themselves, and their native BCB appearance, come from BCBPak. BCBPak must therefore be installed and enabled for the BCB add-on to have any effect — without it, [font=Courier New]ClothMorphBCB[/font] does nothing. (This is separate from the soft-requirement note above, which is about using the BCB [i]body[/i] on NPCs.)
[/list]

[b]For the SCO add-on ([font=Courier New]ClothMorphSCO[/font])[/b] — required [b]only if you install that optional add-on[/b]:
[list]
[*][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/baldursgate3/mods/2617]Scantily Clad Camp Outfits (SCO)[/url], by Crosscrusade — NexusMods mod 2617. The SCO add-on ships [b]only[/b] the SBBF- and BCB-fitted refit meshes for these outfits; the outfits themselves, and their Vanilla appearance, come from the SCO mod. SCO must therefore be installed and enabled for the SCO add-on to have any effect — without it, [font=Courier New]ClothMorphSCO[/font] does nothing. (The base Body and Clothing Morph mod does [b]not[/b] need SCO; this requirement applies only to the optional SCO add-on.)
[/list]

[size=4][b]Installation[/b][/size]
[list]
[*]Install the hard requirements above.
[*]Install Body and Clothing Morph with your mod manager.
[*]Load order: load Body and Clothing Morph (the ClothMorph paks) [b]ABOVE BCB[/b] in the load order.
[/list]

[spoiler=For the technically curious — load order]Internal component paks:
[list]
[*][b]ClothMorphRuntime[/b] — the engine / Script Extender logic.
[*][b]ClothMorphContent[/b] — the Vanilla/SBBF refit meshes (~405 garments).
[*][b]ClothMorphBCB[/b] — the BCB clothing add-on. Requires BCBPak by Sindae (NexusMods 2351) to be installed and enabled.
[*][b]ClothMorphSCO[/b] (optional) — Scantily Clad Camp Outfits add-on. Requires the Scantily Clad Camp Outfits mod (NexusMods 2617) to be installed and enabled.
[/list][/spoiler]

[size=4][b]How to use[/b][/size]
[b]MCM:[/b] Open the Mod Configuration Menu and use the "Body shape" radio picker to choose Vanilla, SBBF, or BCB for the currently controlled character.

[b]Hotkeys:[/b] In MCM keybindings, bind the "cycle body" key and/or the direct-set keys for Vanilla / SBBF / BCB. These are unbound by default — set them to whatever you like. (Requires MCM 1.19 or newer.)

[b]Console:[/b] Use commands such as [font=Courier New]!cm_setbody vanilla[/font], [font=Courier New]!cm_setbody sbbf[/font], or [font=Courier New]!cm_setbody bcb[/font], plus the diagnostic commands.

[size=4][b]Coverage & Limitations[/b][/size]
As of initial release:
[list]
[*]Vanilla and SBBF bodies: broad vanilla clothing coverage with SCO optional add-on (the ClothMorphContent set, ~405 garments).
[*]BCB body/clothing: in progress. Some BCB items are validated for use with non-BCB bodies via this mod. Some will only fit BCB bodies, or will apply the BCB body regardless of the mod setting.
[/list]

[b]Known limitations:[/b]
[list]
[*]On the BCB body, some draped/slinky dresses conform only approximately (the refit is a reverse-deform, kept conservative to avoid flattening the dress's flare).
[*]Some garments that bake their own body into the mesh (e.g. the "Full Metal Dress" / CorsetSkirtArm) intentionally render as their original BCB version and do not morph — this is by design, to avoid a worse artifact.
[*]The "Shar Leggings + Oathbreaker Heels" outfit is excluded (the body morph does not apply to it in testing).
[*]Female human/elf/half-elf/drow bodies only (HUM_F). Other races and body types are not yet covered.
[*]Multiplayer support is limited/experimental.
[/list]

[size=4][b]For mod authors[/b][/size]
Other clothing-mod authors can opt their items in to automatic refitting by shipping a small marker file named [font=Courier New]ClothMorphPermission.json[/font] inside their pak (under [font=Courier New]Mods/<TheirModFolder>/[/font]). It records their explicit permission, the credit line they want shown, and which bodies/items are in scope.

No third-party assets are adapted without the author's permission either posted or otherwise provided, and the author's credit line ships verbatim. The full spec is in the mod's docs.

[size=4][b]Permissions[/b][/size]
This mod is FREE and must always stay free; it is not for sale. Donation Points are fine.

